<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8268480>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Nausithoe punctata. A—Original drawing by B. Werner of the polyp colony inside a sponge. B—Colony in Sant’Angelo, Naples, Italy; only the terminal end of the polyps, with the tentacle crown, is visible (photo: © Fabio Russo 2017). C–F: NMNH 57654. C—Aboral view of adult medusa showing the gastrovascular cavity (gc). D—Oral view of adult medusa showing the mouth (mo) with manubrium. E—Detail of the gastrovascular cavity showing the gastric filaments (gf), gonads (g) and coronal groove (cg). F—Detail of the rhopalium (rh), with statocyst (s) and ocellus (e)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8268480/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

